      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:54:1",
      "text": [
        " قَضَى أَمِيرُ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ ( عليه السلام ) فِي عَيْنِ فَرَسٍ فُقِئَتْ عَيْنُهَا بِرُبُعِ ثَمَنِهَا يَوْمَ فُقِئَتْ عَيْنُهَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Najran, from Aasim Bin Humeyd, from Muhammad Bin Qays, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Amir Al-Momineen<sup>asws</sup> judged regarding an eye of a horse which was blinded (by someone), by a quarter of its price on the day its eye was blinded (price when horse had both eyes)’."
        ]
      }
